headline: Cadence Design Systems’s (NASDAQ:CDNS) Q3 Sales Top Estimates
summary: Electronic design automation company Cadence Design Systems (NASDAQ:CDNS) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q3 CY2025, with sales up 10.1% year on year to $1.34 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.93 per share was 7.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Cadence: Q3 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of nine analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $1.79 per share. The maker of hardware and software products for validating chip designs posted revenue of $1.34 billion in the period, also beating Street forecasts. Eight analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $1.33 billion.

headline: Can Cadence’s 36.5% Rally Continue After Recent AI Partnership Push?
summary: If you’re eyeing Cadence Design Systems and wondering if now is the time to make a move, you’re not alone. The stock has rewarded patient investors with a remarkable 212.3% gain over the past five years, and it is up an impressive 36.5% in the last year alone. Even after some recent ups and downs, such as a 4.7% increase this week following a slight 1.4% dip over the past month, Cadence continues to draw interest from both seasoned analysts and new investors looking for innovative tech...
